119-145 West 17th Street, North side, between Sixth and Seventh Avenues.
about 1922.
Edwin Levick.

Sixth Avenue at N. E. corner of 17th Street.
March 22, 1935.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

Sixth Avenue at N. E. corner of 17th Street.
March 22, 1935.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

Sixth Avenue, east side, north across West 17th Street. The gas station appearing is at the S. E. corner. This permits details of buildings at the N. E. corner to be clearly observed. View No. 3 is limited to this corner.

The earlier view is photographed during the period while the old 6th Avenue "El" darkened the Avenue. View 2 is taken immediately after demolition of same.

The ornate structure above 18th Street is the former Seigel-Cooper Department Store. This institution widely publicized the phrase "Meet me at the fountain." This was derived from the presence of a magnificent interior fountain and stairway. During the World War,(1917-18) this structure was utilized as a hospital.
